earest family,<br>
<br>
Yes, family, as that's what I've considered you all since I joined you.  Of course now I guess it's just time for this kid to move on to college.  Will it mean that I lose touch and will be forever studying or getting into bar fights?  NO!  I hope to keep up a great amount of communication (better than the typical college student does with his/her family), both on the boards here and through direct tells in-game.  I was happy Tormenter and Fromunder were on when the time came for me to /guildremove, just to have someone to say good-bye to.<br>
<br>
I can't wait for the day to come that we can all group together again.  I probably won't level as quickly, for a few reasons.  First of all, well, I can only gain 8 more levels now, and these 51+ levels apparently take a while.  Secondly, guild raids are not exactly experience friendly, as there will usually be only a couple of groups out of many that are putting out enough damage to actually get experience.  And last but not least, I would like to play my other characters more so I can be around you all.<br>
<br>
Well anyway, I'll miss the ease of communication we once had in game, but I'll try my best to keep up with tells and everything.  I'll keep up my profile and also give some posts here whenever something exciting happens.  Last night was an exp night, so I went to The Hole for the second time, then after that was done, I went to Sebilis for the first time.  I got some decent loot as well, Loam Encrusted choker from the Hole that I'll use after my INT reaches 200 as it gives AC and mana, with some CHA and some other stuff.  I also got an Elemental Binder (5 to AC/INT/SV FIRE, mage only).  After we moved to Sebilis, I got a diamond and a couple other lesser gems, as well as another copy of a spell for me to turn in.  But wow, a diamond!  Okay, bye for now my friends, I will talk to you soon.<br>
<br>
Loralana Mystere<br>
